Reactions

Source: R/reactions.R
reactions.Rd

A data set containing the metadata associated with each qPCR well and respective reaction mix. Data is obtained from Ruijter (2013), doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2012.08.011 but original source is by Vermeulen (2009), doi:10.1016/S1470-2045(09)70154-8 .

Usage

reactions()

Source

  • https://medischebiologie.nl/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/qpcrdatamethods.zip

  • https://github.com/ramiromagno/vermeulen/blob/main/data-raw/reactions.csv.gz

Value

A data frame with 24,576 reactions and 5 variables:

plate

Plate identifier. Because one plate was used per gene, the name of the plate is the same as the values in target.

well

Well identifier.

dye

In all reactions the SYBR Green I master mix (Roche) was used, so the value is always "SYBR".

sample

Sample identifier.

target

Target.

Details

The tidy version of the data is kept at the repository of the source of {vermeulen} package. This function fetches such data and thus requires internet connection.

See also

amplification_curves() targets() samples()
